article.description: Joseph Lanzi had a career-high 20 points as Denver defeated Utah Valley 74-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Lanzi scores 20 to carry Denver past Utah Valley 74-62
article.linkText: Lanzi scores 20 to carry Denver past Utah Valley 74-62
article.story: DENVER -- Joseph Lanzi had a career-high 20 points as Denver defeated Utah Valley 74-62 on Saturday. Jase Townsend had 18 points and Ade Murkey added six rebounds for Denver (1-1). Brandon Averette had 17 points for the Wolverines (1-1). Trey Woodbury added 12 points and six rebounds and Isaiah White had 9 points and 10 rebounds. Denver matches up against Utah State on the road on Tuesday. Utah Valley takes on Ottawa (AZ) at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
